Uses of Package
blocks

  • Packages that use blocks 
    Package Description
    blocks  
  • Classes in blocks used by blocks 
    Class and Description
    BentWire
    Bent wire blocks are one of four kinds of wires, which transmit signals without affecting or being affected by them.
    CornerPipe
    Corner pipes are one of three basic kinds of pipes, which supply blocks and items to powered devices they are attached to.
    EndWire
    End wire blocks are one of four kinds of wires, which transmit signals without affecting or being affected by them.
    FiveWayPipe
    Five-way pipes are one of three basic kinds of pipes, which supply blocks and items to powered devices they are attached to.
    JunctionWire
    Junction wire blocks are one of four kinds of wires, which transmit signals without affecting or being affected by them.
    Pipe
    Pipes are devices that will draw items from components and deliver them to components that use them.
    PowerStick
    Power sticks are special components that will supply power if and only if they are not powered themselves.
    PressSwitch
    Press switches are components that can be set to supply or not supply a current at the user's control.
    StraightPipe
    Straight pipes are one of three basic kinds of pipes, which supply blocks and items to powered devices they are attached to.
    StraightWire
    Straight wire blocks are one of four kinds of wires, which transmit signals without affecting or being affected by them.
    Wire
    Wires are basic components that transfer signals without affecting them or being affected by them.
